					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Alright, I think I'm gonna try and impersonate <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/moto42" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=175861&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1587602603" alt="Moto42" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=175861)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/moto42" >Moto42</a></span>. I know this author was never as prominent as many others, but what he has written is very highly rated (one of his articles is approaching +6000!). He was one of the authors that really laid the groundwork for the wiki, and his style is incredibly distinct and easy to recognize. You can look at any of his articles on the site and immediately say, &quot;That article was made by Moto, no doubt about it.&quot;</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
